Discover two hallucination cases when using a generative AI system.

1. ChatGPT Fake Legal Cases (Mata v. Avianca, 2023)
Observation: A lawyer used ChatGPT to prepare a legal brief, but the AI generated completely fake case citations, 
which were submitted to court and later discovered to be non-existent.

2. ChatGPT Defamation Hallucination Case (2023)
Observation: ChatGPT falsely accused a real person of fraud in a generated summary of a legal case, 
leading to a defamation lawsuit due to fabricated information presented as fact.

